Author: ComputerGenie ğŸ‘´ğŸ¼ğŸ“¢#7004
Content:
â€œram staker â€œ is the name james gave to the PoS staking mechanism in komodo 
iirc, it's because it does most of the processing "in ram" in advance of actual block time

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: not exactly

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: What it does is load the walelts unspents and everything it needs to stake with them into an array

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: then it will re use that array

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: until it finds a block, or 10 minutes expires

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: then it clears it and reloads the wallet

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: It stops someone dwy attacking the wallet with dust to prevent you staking blocks.

Author: blackjok3r#3181
Content: and also with vast amounts of utxos its just loads faster.
